{"id":1271128284,"question_id":2,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"3 weeks, 6 days","timestamp":1716964392,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"1 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1271128284/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Add Two Numbers","memory":"44.1 MB","code":"/**\n * Definition for singly-linked list.\n * public class ListNode {\n *     int val;\n *     ListNode next;\n *     ListNode() {}\n *     ListNode(int val) { this.val = val; }\n *     ListNode(int val, ListNode next) { this.val = val; this.next = next; }\n * }\n */\nclass Solution {\n    public ListNode addTwoNumbers(ListNode l1, ListNode l2) {\n        ListNode res = new ListNode();\n        ListNode cur = res;\n        int sum = 0, carry=0;\n        \n        while(l1!=null && l2!=null){\n            sum = carry+l1.val+l2.val;\n            cur.next = new ListNode(sum%10);\n            cur = cur.next;\n            carry = sum/10;\n            \n            l1 = l1.next;\n            l2 = l2.next;\n        }\n        \n        while(l1!=null ){\n            sum = carry+l1.val;\n            cur.next = new ListNode(sum%10);\n            cur = cur.next;\n            carry = sum/10;\n            l1 = l1.next;\n        }\n        \n        while(l2!=null){\n            sum = carry+l2.val;\n            cur.next = new ListNode(sum%10);\n            cur = cur.next;\n            carry = sum/10;\n            l2 = l2.next;\n        }\n        \n        if(carry!=0){\n            cur.next = new ListNode(carry);\n        }\n        \n        return res.next;\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"add-two-numbers","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
